<TITLE> Rajuk lottery, scheduled for Wednesday, still awaits approval </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 14 (bdnews24.com)A Rajuk lottery for residential plots in Uttara and Purbachal, scheduled for Wednesday, is yet to receive final approval from the housing and public works ministry. "Preparations to draw the lottery on Rajuk's behalf are complete, but we cannot finalise the matter without ministry approval," Rajuk's acting chairman Golam Kibria told bdnews24.com on Monday. Kibria said the lottery would have to be drawn after Eid if no decision was taken on the matter soon. The lottery for applicants in four categories'artist', 'judge', 'freedom fighter' and 'expatriate'are set to be drawn Wednesday. Rajuk, the capital's development authority, invited applicants to the lottery for Uttara and Purbachal plots last November under a total of thirteen categories. The authorities firstly set Dec 18 as the deadline for applications and then extended it twice up to Apr 30. Rajuk figures show a total of 113,000 aspirants for plots under the Purbachal project and 42,000 for plots under the Uttara project in a total of 13 categories. The Uttara project (third phase) has 800 plots on offer while the Purbachal project has 8000 plots. bdnews24
